UBUNTU_15.04
[sudo] pip install virtualenv

virtualenv ~/PerosnalBlog/env             OR
virtualenv -p python3.5 --no-site-packages env

https://www.dabapps.com/blog/introduction-to-pip-and-virtualenv-python/
cd ~/PerosnalBlog/

to activate your current version of python
source env/bin/activate

to deactivate:
source env/bin/deactivate

which python ?

after: source env/bin/activate

pip install pelican
pip install Markdown

Fire up your demo project:
pelican-quickstart



create some test post in folder content:
Title: My First Post
Date: 2014-12-20 10:20
Category: Electronics

My first demo post :-)

and save it as 'demo_post.md' (Markdown style)



run:
pelican content 

go to: cd Desktop/PersonalBlog/output/  folder
and run python -m pelican.server


////////////////////////igbt6.github.io SETUP///////////////////////////////////////////////
Clone the repository

Go to the folder where you want to store your project, and clone the new repository:

git clone https://github.com/igbt6/igbt6.github.io
Hello World

Enter the project folder and add an index.html file:

cd igbt6.github.io

echo "Hello World" > index.html
Push it

Add, commit, and push your changes:

git add --all

git commit -m "Initial commit"

git push -u origin master
â€¦and you're done!

Fire up a browser and go to http://igbt6.github.io.
